race.description: Mayhem In The Mounting Yard 21St Nov Plate (C4)
race.comment: Competitive. EARENDEL (1) resumes off a hat-trick and is proven fresh. He's trialled strongly at the track and has scope for further improvement. He's won 4/6 and can add to that record this evening. GARCON D'ESPOIR (2) brought strong synthetic form to resumption and looked a run short at this track/trip. May need a touch longer now, but he's won 2/4 second up and it wouldn't surprise to see him right in the finish. WHIPPIN PICCADILLY (8) deserved her comfortable CL3 with this track/trip. Among the best players again. THE LONGEST YARD (3) missed a whisker this trip at Hobart second-up as favourite. Finds a touch easier and maps for the run of the race. He has claims as well.
